Use [account.updateEmojiStatus](https://core.telegram.org/method/account.updateEmojiStatus) to change the status emoji of your profile.

*   Pass [emojiStatus](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/emojiStatus) to set a [custom emoji](https://core.telegram.org/api/custom-emoji).
*   Pass [emojiStatusUntil](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/emojiStatusUntil) to set a [custom emoji](https://core.telegram.org/api/custom-emoji), for a limited period of time.
*   Pass [emojiStatusEmpty](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/emojiStatusEmpty) to set the default Premium badge.

The newly set [EmojiStatus](https://core.telegram.org/type/EmojiStatus) constructor will be contained in the `emoji_status` field of the [user](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/user) constructor, and other users will receive an [updateUserEmojiStatus](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/updateUserEmojiStatus).

Other logged-in clients will also receive an [updateRecentEmojiStatuses](https://core.telegram.org/constructor/updateRecentEmojiStatuses) update, indicating that the recent status emoji list has changed.

Recently used emoji statuses can be fetched using [account.getRecentEmojiStatuses](https://core.telegram.org/method/account.getRecentEmojiStatuses), and the list can be cleared using [account.clearRecentEmojiStatuses](https://core.telegram.org/method/account.clearRecentEmojiStatuses).

Note that the custom emoji selection UI should offer a list of categories to quickly filter results by a (list of) emojis, or by some other criteria, see [here »](https://core.telegram.org/api/emoji-categories) for more info.

